<h1>🧭 Tourist Booking Platform</h1>

<p>This is a full-stack .NET web application designed to showcase core backend and frontend development skills for a Junior .NET Developer position.</p>

<hr />

<h3>🎯 Project Goals</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Build a realistic e-tourism event booking platform</li>
    <li>Demonstrate understanding of full CRUD in a layered architecture</li>
    <li>Use modern .NET Core technologies (Web API + MVC)</li>
    <li>Deploy and maintain a live version using CI/CD (GitHub Actions + Azure)</li>
</ul>

<h3>🛠 Technologies Used</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Backend:</strong> ASP.NET Core Web API (C#), Entity Framework Core</li>
    <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> ASP.NET Core MVC, Razor, Bootstrap 5</li>
    <li><strong>Database:</strong> SQL Server (LocalDB for dev, Azure SQL for prod)</li>
    <li><strong>DevOps:</strong> GitHub Actions, Azure App Service (2 projects deployed)</li>
</ul>

<h3>🧩 Features</h3>
<ul>
    <li>View list of tourist events (public-facing)</li>
    <li>Make reservations as a user (name/email form)</li>
    <li>Admin panel with login (admin/admin) to Create, Edit, Delete events</li>
    <li>Form validation, error handling, retry logic, and basic authentication</li>
</ul>

